Firefighters in Durban have had their hands full on Monday, battling a blaze that started in the early hours of the morning in Overport. It's not known what caused the fire, which ripped through two buildings. Reporter Mawande Kheswa has more. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Firefighters in Durban have had their hands full on Monday, battling a blaze that started in the early hours of the morning in Overport. It's not known what caused the fire, which ripped through two buildings. Although no loss of life was reported, a firefighter was injured in the blaze. Authorities are still investigating the cause of the fire. * eNCA'sÂ Mawande Kheswa reports.